> Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Mexican Style Spiced Beef Chilli in a Bun in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Add the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} to the mince.

Bring to the boil then simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, slice the @Brioche Hot Dog Buns{2} down through the middle (but not all the way through).

In a #bowl{}, combine the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}, @Baby Leaf Mix{20%g} and @Mayonnaise{32%g}.

Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy!

Transfer the hot dog buns to your plates.

Fill with the mince and sprinkle over the cheese.

Serve the baby leaf slaw alongside.

Enjoy!